    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is fine overall. I suggest adding this patch below. It will enable players who have the setting disabled to still view target lines by pressing the Alt key.\n\n``` diff\ndiff --git a/OpenRA.Game/Graphics/TargetLineRenderable.cs b/OpenRA.Game/Graphics/TargetLineRenderable.cs\nindex d869658..a177d9c 100644\n--- a/OpenRA.Game/Graphics/TargetLineRenderable.cs\n+++ b/OpenRA.Game/Graphics/TargetLineRenderable.cs\n@@ -47,8 +47,7 @@ public void Render(WorldRenderer wr)\n                        var a = first;\n                        foreach (var b in waypoints.Skip(1).Select(pos => wr.ScreenPxPosition(pos)))\n                        {\n-                               if (Game.Settings.Game.DrawTargetLine)\n-                                       Game.Renderer.WorldLineRenderer.DrawLine(a, b, color);\n+                               Game.Renderer.WorldLineRenderer.DrawLine(a, b, color);\n                                wr.DrawTargetMarker(color, b);\n                                a = b;\n                        }\ndiff --git a/OpenRA.Game/Traits/DrawLineToTarget.cs b/OpenRA.Game/Traits/DrawLineToTarget.cs\nindex e0923ac..0e4f4ca 100644\n--- a/OpenRA.Game/Traits/DrawLineToTarget.cs\n+++ b/OpenRA.Game/Traits/DrawLineToTarget.cs\n@@ -64,6 +64,9 @@ public IEnumerable<IRenderable> RenderAfterWorld(WorldRenderer wr)\n                        if ((lifetime <= 0 || --lifetime <= 0) && !force)\n                                yield break;\n\n+                       if (!(force || Game.Settings.Game.DrawTargetLine))\n+                               yield break;\n+\n                        if (targets == null || targets.Count == 0)\n                                yield break;\n\ndiff --git a/mods/ra/chrome/settings.yaml b/mods/ra/chrome/settings.yaml\nindex a6dc9a3..f01ec21 100644\n--- a/mods/ra/chrome/settings.yaml\n+++ b/mods/ra/chrome/settings.yaml\n@@ -205,7 +205,7 @@ Background@SETTINGS_PANEL:\n                                        Text: Always Show Status Bars\n                                Checkbox@DISPLAY_TARGET_LINES_CHECKBOX:\n                                        X: 310\n-                                       Y: 260\n+                                       Y: 265\n                                        Width: 200\n                                        Height: 20\n                                        Font: Regular\n\n```\n"
  },
